ACT iv, SCENE 2

The hired impostor, not seeing Charmides, soliloquizes on the part he has assumed. Charmides makes fun of him and finally sends him off, utterly baffied.

The scene is full of vis comica, and is probably the original of that amusing one in Shakspere’s Tamz'ny of the Shrew (V. 1), where the Pedant, disguised as Vincentio, encounters the real Vincentio.
